    <text id="B0315T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell criticizes Jackson for the late submission of two purchase
                accounts.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District,
                    Department of the Potomac
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Thos P. Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-07-20">July 20th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your communication of 18th inst. inclosing accounts of Henry A. Harner and Lewis
                    W. Pearce has been received.</p>

                <p>The account of Harner is per purchases, made on the 21st of June last, and you
                    will please explain why said account was not forwarded in the month when
                    purchased, as enjoined in instructions from this office.</p>

                <p>It is now too late to take up these articles on my Return for June, and the
                    account will have to be altered to July.</p>

                <p>Hereafter you will take particular pains to see that such accounts are sent in
                    before the 25th of the month in which the purchases are made or services
                    rendered.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
